8. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS.
8.1 Foreground IP. Any inventions, works of authorship, designs, methodologies, software code, or other intellectual property created by Service Provider in the performance of the Services (“Foreground IP”) shall be jointly owned by the Parties. Each Party hereby grants to the other an irrevocable, worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license to use, reproduce, and modify the Foreground IP for its internal business operations.
8.2 Pre-Existing IP. Service Provider retains all right, title, and interest in any pre-existing tools, libraries, or methodologies used in the delivery of Services, provided such pre-existing IP is listed in Schedule C. Client receives a perpetual, non-transferable license solely to the extent necessary to use the Services deliverables.

12. CONFIDENTIALITY.
12.1 Definition. “Confidential Information” includes all non-public pricing, business plans, client data, and the terms of this Agreement. The receiving Party shall protect Confidential Information using at least the same degree of care it uses for its own sensitive information